org.codehaus.xfire.handler
Interface Handler

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractHandler, AbstractJAXWSHandler, AbstractWSS4JHandler, AddressingInHandler, AddressingOutHandler, ClientFaultConverter, CloseMessageHandler, CorrelatorHandler, CustomFaultHandler, DefaultFaultHandler, DispatchServiceHandler, DOMInHandler, DOMOutHandler, FaultSender, FaultSoapSerializerHandler, HandlerPipeline, LocateBindingHandler, LoggingHandler, MessageHandler, OutMessageSender, PostInvocationHandler, ReadHeadersHandler, ServiceInvocationHandler, SoapActionInHandler, SoapActionOutHandler, SoapBodyHandler, SoapSerializerHandler, ValidateHeadersHandler, WebFaultHandler, WSS4JInHandler, WSS4JOutHandler, XFireServletController.FaultResponseCodeHandler, XMPPFaultHandler
public interface Handler

A handler is just something that processes an XML message.

If an exception occurrs in the invoke method, the entity which started the invocation, is responsible for turning the exception into a fault.

Since:
Feb 18, 2004
Author:
